<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUL 94 / Pounds 1.5m libel award against magazine
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An award-winning boat designer, his wife and their company yesterday won
Pounds 1.485m libel damages in the High Court over a trade magazine article
and editorial comment on their revolutionary Planesail trimaran design.
The amount is the second highest jury award in England after the Pounds 1.5m
awarded to Lord Aldington in 1989 over allegations about his war conduct.
Mr John Walker, his wife Jean and Walker Wingsail Systems, based in
Plymouth, Devon, sued Yachting World, published by IPC Magazines. The
magazine, which also faces costs, denied libel and has said it will appeal.
