<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUL 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Auctions are in recess in Australia until the end of this month and raw wool
costs in the meantime are measured by what merchants assess in relation to
business and the market prospect. No weakness is apparent at present. On the
contrary, with stockpile sales again at encouraging levels last week, and
the Garnaut disposal quotas effectively taken up for July and August
already, the outlook appears at least firm. There was also good demand in
Europe not only for stockpile wool, but for stockpiled tops which were
combed some time ago on behalf of the Australian Wool Corporation then in
charge. This adds to the impression that combs at present are busy on
present orders and there is little or no slack to be taken up to meet
short-term buying interest. Prices are without wool auction guidance but
must be described as firm.
</TEXT>
