<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUL 94 / International Company News: Gantry builds holding in Bridge
Oil
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The battle for Bridge Oil, the Sydney-based energy group, threatened to
reach stalemate last night. Gantry Acquisition, one of the two rival
US-based bidders, raised its stake in Bridge to almost 10 per cent, buying
shares at prices ranging up to 95 cents.
Gantry said it wished to proceed with a full takeover offer at 95 cents a
share - which would value Bridge at ADollars 399m (USDollars 285m) - but
required further information before it would do so. In particular, it wanted
to know if its Texan rival, Parker &amp; Parsley, would accept a higher Gantry
offer in respect of its own 21 per cent stake in Bridge.
Until yesterday, Gantry had been offering 85 cents a share for Bridge, while
P&amp;P was offering 90 cents a share.
P&amp;P described Gantry's 'alleged wish to make a 95 cents a share
highly-conditional offer' as 'a mirage'.
It said it would not accept such an offer in respect of its own Bridge
shares.
Gantry insisted it had no intention of accepting P&amp;P's 90 cents offer, and
accused P&amp;P of using delaying tactics.
