FT  08 JUL 94 / US forces stage Haiti invasion exercise
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JEREMY KAHN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Pentagon yesterday confirmed reports that more than 1,000 elite special
forces troops staged exercises two weeks ago in the south-east US and Gulf
of Mexico designed to simulate an invasion of Haiti, writes Jeremy Kahn from
Washington. Similar rehearsals were conducted before the US invasion of
Panama in 1989. The White House insists it is still pursuing economic
sanctions against Haiti's military junta and that armed intervention is not
imminent. A Navy amphibious assault group carrying 2,000 Marines meanwhile,
set sail yesterday for Haiti's waters, where it will be on station in the
event US citizens or other foreigners need to be evacuated from the troubled
country.
